h: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/c0712c5bb4535653fe1b0654235ea0ef.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Rook looks at something off-screen with Varric behind him.\" data-chomp-id=\"c0712c5bb4535653fe1b0654235ea0ef\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"1080\" data-alt=\"Rook looks at something off-screen with Varric behind him.\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/c0712c5bb4535653fe1b0654235ea0ef.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eScreenshot: BioWare / Kotaku\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"c0712c5bb4535653fe1b0654235ea0ef\" data-recommend-id=\"image://c0712c5bb4535653fe1b0654235ea0ef\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Rook looks at something off-screen with Varric behind him.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eWith every new report about \u003cem\u003eDragon Age: The Veilguard\u003c/em\u003e’s troubled development, it feels like a miracle that the game came out at all. A new story from \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;External link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-06-11/inside-the-dragon-age-debacle-that-gutted-ea-s-bioware-studio?embedded-checkout=true\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-06-11/inside-the-dragon-age-debacle-that-gutted-ea-s-bioware-studio?embedded-checkout=true\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eBloomberg\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e outlines how the \u003cem\u003eDragon Age \u003c/em\u003eteam was jerked around by publisher Electronic Arts and forced to make pivots with limited resources and time, making it impossible for the RPG to complete the sort of holistic retooling it would have received under more reasonable circumstances. Reading this and seeing how, \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-veilguard-bioware-mass-effect-team-ending-1851784319\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-veilguard-bioware-mass-effect-team-ending-1851784319\"\u003eafter all that strife\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e, the team was still demolished and subsequently \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-veilguard-mass-effect-5-bioware-live-service-1851756169\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-veilguard-mass-effect-5-bioware-live-service-1851756169\"\u003ethrown under the bus\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e, it feels like BioWare was set up to fail, and it bore the consequences of its publisher’s poor decisions. - Kenneth Shepard \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-the-veilguard-bioware-layoffs-mass-effect-1851784416?_gl=1*1swiv1l*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*czE3NDk4NDQwMzkkbzY0MCRnMSR0MTc0OTg0NTcxMCRqNTQkbDAkaDA.\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/dragon-age-the-veilguard-bioware-layoffs-mass-effect-1851784416?_gl=1*1swiv1l*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*czE3NDk4NDQwMzkkbzY0MCRnMSR0MTc0OTg0NTcxMCRqNTQkbDAkaDA.\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"1154349b0c8428f85f8b643b368f2a24\" data-recommend-id=\"image://1154349b0c8428f85f8b643b368f2a24\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1200\" data-height=\"675\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Hugh and Diana look at something off-screen.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"Hugh and Diana look at something off-screen.\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/1154349b0c8428f85f8b643b368f2a24.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/1154349b0c8428f85f8b643b368f2a24.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/1154349b0c8428f85f8b643b368f2a24.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Hugh and Diana look at something off-screen.\" data-chomp-id=\"1154349b0c8428f85f8b643b368f2a24\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"675\" data-alt=\"Hugh and Diana look at something off-screen.\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/1154349b0c8428f85f8b643b368f2a24.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: Capcom\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"1154349b0c8428f85f8b643b368f2a24\" data-recommend-id=\"image://1154349b0c8428f85f8b643b368f2a24\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1200\" data-height=\"675\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Hugh and Diana look at something off-screen.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eI had forgotten all about \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/capcom-pragmata-delay-delayed-2023-2024-ps5-xbox-pc-1850531732\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/capcom-pragmata-delay-delayed-2023-2024-ps5-xbox-pc-1850531732\"\u003e\u003cem\u003ePragmata\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003cem\u003e \u003c/em\u003eby the time Capcom was setting up appointments to play the puzzle shooter at Summer Game Fest. We’re five years removed from its original announcement, and Capcom is no stranger to quietly hiding a game away and never releasing it (remember \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/dragons-dogma-2-caves-deep-down-capcom-1851364378\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/dragons-dogma-2-caves-deep-down-capcom-1851364378\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eDeep Down\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e?). So, I let the game disappear from my memory until its name showed up in my inbox. Perhaps it’s fitting then that \u003cem\u003ePragmata \u003c/em\u003efeels a bit like a game out of time, as its gruff old man protagonist, slow-moving enemies, and brutalist sci-fi aesthetic are all evocative of the over-the-shoulder shooters from the PS360 era. Given those seemingly bygone qualities, it’d be easy for \u003cem\u003ePragmata \u003c/em\u003eto feel rote and dated, but what I played was just inventive enough to feel novel. I was super impressed with it. - Kenneth Shepard \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/pragmata-capcom-preview-summer-game-fest-impressions-1851784342?_gl=1*16jz1mu*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*czE3NDk4NDQwMzkkbzY0MCRnMSR0MTc0OTg0NTcxMCRqNTQkbDAkaDA.\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/pragmata-capcom-preview-summer-game-fest-impressions-1851784342?_gl=1*16jz1mu*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*czE3NDk4NDQwMzkkbzY0MCRnMSR0MTc0OTg0NTcxMCRqNTQkbDAkaDA.\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"68a5e24c09aade8b847d9af3d4fd0f24\" data-recommend-id=\"image://68a5e24c09aade8b847d9af3d4fd0f24\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"A collage of various tie-in popcorn buckets, including Dune, Saw X, Barbie, Ghostbusters, Ant-Man, Guardians of the Galaxy, and Star Wars.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"A collage of various tie-in popcorn buckets, including Dune, Saw X, Barbie, Ghostbusters, Ant-Man, Guardians of the Galaxy, and Star Wars.\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"in-house-art\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/68a5e24c09aade8b847d9af3d4fd0f24.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/68a5e24c09aade8b847d9af3d4fd0f24.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/68a5e24c09aade8b847d9af3d4fd0f24.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A collage of various tie-in popcorn buckets, including Dune, Saw X, Barbie, Ghostbusters, Ant-Man, Guardians of the Galaxy, and Star Wars.\" data-chomp-id=\"68a5e24c09aade8b847d9af3d4fd0f24\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"1080\" data-alt=\"A collage of various tie-in popcorn buckets, including Dune, Saw X, Barbie, Ghostbusters, Ant-Man, Guardians of the Galaxy, and Star Wars.\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/68a5e24c09aade8b847d9af3d4fd0f24.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: AMC Theatres / Cinemark / Kotaku\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"68a5e24c09aade8b847d9af3d4fd0f24\" data-recommend-id=\"image://68a5e24c09aade8b847d9af3d4fd0f24\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"A collage of various tie-in popcorn buckets, including Dune, Saw X, Barbie, Ghostbusters, Ant-Man, Guardians of the Galaxy, and Star Wars.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eAs it turns out, the \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/dune-part-two-sandworm-bucket-interview-1851288147\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/dune-part-two-sandworm-bucket-interview-1851288147\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eDune: Part Two\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/dune-2-popcorn-bucket-sandworm-1851215982\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/dune-2-popcorn-bucket-sandworm-1851215982\"\u003esandworm-shaped monstrosity\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e that AMC passed off as a popcorn bucket wasn’t the only one of its kind. In fact, since 2019, AMC has apparently \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;External link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/popcorn-buckets-dune-star-wars-movie-theater-revenue-1235824026/\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/popcorn-buckets-dune-star-wars-movie-theater-revenue-1235824026/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003emade a killing\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e selling all kinds of collectible tie-in buckets for the year’s biggest blockbusters, from \u003cem\u003eStar Wars: Rise of Skywalker \u003c/em\u003eto \u003cem\u003eTaylor Swift: Eras Tour\u003c/em\u003e. This year, they’ve been making a killing by selling buckets themed after a bunch of blockbusters and family-centric movies, which tend to bring in huge audiences that live and die for this kind of stuff. It’s all a racket, I tells ya, but a racket that has spawned a bigger market than I was led to believe. Cinemark and other movie theater chains have also jumped on the train, and by now there are folks with a sizeable-enough bunch of these buckets at home to call it an honest-to-goodness \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;External link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://www.reddit.com/r/AMCsAList/comments/16llrzk/my_popcorn_bucket_collection_has_grown_a_bit/?utm_source=embedv2\u0026amp;utm_medium=post_embed\u0026amp;utm_content=post_body\u0026amp;embed_host_url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-features/movie-buffs-popcorn-bucket-collectors-1234976027/\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/AMCsAList/comments/16llrzk/my_popcorn_bucket_collection_has_grown_a_bit/?utm_source=embedv2\u0026amp;utm_medium=post_embed\u0026amp;utm_content=post_body\u0026amp;embed_host_url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-features/movie-buffs-popcorn-bucket-collectors-1234976027/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003ecollection\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e, and their interest in them an \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;External link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-features/movie-buffs-popcorn-bucket-collectors-1234976027/\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026